 _Description_:

Since we need to show many images(_coding in base64_) in one cell's output area, the reload of _.ipynb_ file will be extremely slow. While the outputs of the cell might contain other useful messages that must be left, _only_ a part of outputs needs to be cleared up. 
```python
def _create_nb_img(tag_id, data):
    display(HTML("<img id='{}' src='data:image/png;base64,{}'/>".format(tag_id, data)))


def _replace_nb_img(tag_id, data):
    js = "$('#{}').attr('src', 'data:image/png;base64,{}')".format(tag_id, data.replace("\n", ""))
    display(Javascript(js))

# usage
# get_image_data() will load a new image every time
_create_nb_img(tag_id, get_image_data(0))
for i in range(1, 1000):
    _replace_nb_img(tag_id, get_image_data(i))
```

_**Notice**: As the visual effects to the user are similar to the video via picture replacement, and the output of images files might and even must be especially huge, the reload of notebook is not user-friendly..._
  
So our demands are: 
